<br>
It turns out this is not true. It happens but it happens rarely, and people get stabbed to death with intent as well.<br>
<br>
People are social animals and their base impulse is to _dominate_ not slaughter. Why do you think military training is the way it is? It is a form of brainwashing the intent is NOT primarily to get people to stay in a scary situation, people will do this from peer pressure and loyalty and love and honor. Most men will naturally not run when trouble happens if their friends or family are left behind. This is instinctual, evolutionarily ingrained behavior. You see it in EQ all the time, people die when they should have run because group member was left behind. It's not universal but it happens a LOT. And this is merely a 2d simulation.<br>
<br>
The urge to kill generally however has to be taught. Why do you think gang inititations are the way they are? Or why do you think the process of becoming a made mafiosa is the way it is?<br>
<br>
It is because in general humans are not inclined to kill until their minds have been warped a certain way.<br>
<br>
To get most normal people to kill you have to face them with a situation where they know it is life or death, and even THEN many people will meekly die rather than kill.<br>
