&quot;But its simple fact, many folk are NOT very responsible, whether it be with a car, gun or anything else.&quot; - Redorious<br>
<br>
There is a difference between irresponsibility and cold blooded murder. It may please you to think that you are the ultimate predator, only held in check by by the restraining laws of society, but it turns out you are just another Bonobo monkey in a tree screaming loudly and trying to get laid.<br>
<br>
Even in lawless regions it is only the hadrened criminals (in which I include police of an oppressive government) that kill. The rest of society continues on, families survive and only the people inured to violence by one method or another doing the killing. That a very few people trained to violence can cow an entire nation is the very proof of this. Most people are just NOT violent. Humans bluster and bray but they don't kill for the most part. Very few people kill without being taught to. Shout yes, brawl yes, kill no. It's a primate thing.<br>
<br>
I am sorry to hear of that incident but it doesn't change the reality. There are always going to be cases of brutality. You say this brother was a crook, so yes, his job was crime, he had been trained to violence and thus that happenned. Note the 'good' brothers impulse was to _put_ himself in harms way to try to bring peace.<br>
<br>
&quot;You are more likely to be killed by someone you know, you are very likely to be killed by them when drunk or on drugs, it is often a crime of passion of rage, THAT IS A FACT.&quot; - Redorious<br>
<br>
This is natural statistically. For someone to kill you they must be physically close to you to do so. The people physically close to you are generally people you know. I would not draw much from this. It is like saying you are more likely to get into an accident the closer you are to your home. Well of course, you do a greater proportion of your driving close to your home than otherwise.<br>
