<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I'm not following your point here, I'm sorry. - Grindel<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
It's ok let me help you<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  You're saying we should employ a stopgap measure, because it exists and nothing better is available yet. I was pointing out another example of this reasoning which I don't think people would agree with.<br>
<br>
In general just because there is no better solution than a flawed one does not necessarily mean that the flawed one should be employed. The solution must be weighed on it's own merit. You tried to shortcut by saying nothing better exists now. I was just pointing out that isn't valid.<br>
